87232f978e054fcd078b2b/gazebo/sensors/SensorManager.cc?at=gazebo7&fileviewer=file-view-default#SensorManager.cc-171) are also not done in the main thread.\r\n\r\nThis seems to cause the `UNIT_ImagesView_TEST` to be flaky.\r\n\r\nBacktrace:\r\n\r\ngist https://gist.github.com/scpeters/59282015402700256619958e289e82d2", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>In QTestFixture, the server instance is run in a <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/src/gazebo7/gazebo/gui/QTestFixture.cc?at=gazebo7&amp;fileviewer=file-view-default\" rel=\"nofollow\">different thread</a> from the main Qt thread, and therefore the <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/src/f9932187fc9dbaefc687232f978e054fcd078b2b/gazebo/sensors/SensorManager.cc?at=gazebo7&amp;fileviewer=file-view-default#SensorManager.cc-171\" rel=\"nofollow\">image sensor contain updates</a> are also not done in the main thread.</p>\n<p>This seems to cause the <code>UNIT_ImagesView_TEST</code> to be flaky.</p>\n<p>Backtrace:</p>\n<p>gist <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/scpeters/59282015402700256619958e289e82d2\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">https://gist.github.com/scpeters/59282015402700256619958e289e82d2</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "new", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2018-02-01T23:59:02.775380+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2018-02-01T23:59:02.775380+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 2416}